      "text": "After the civil unrest end of 2005 ([[2005 civil unrest in France]]), the government, led by prime minister [[Dominique de Villepin]], announced a new law. Dubbed \"law on equality of chances\", it created the [[First Employment Contract]] as well as manual apprenticeship from as early as 14 years of age. From this age, students are allowed to quit the compulsory school system in order to quickly learn a vocation. "
